        Reporting to the Senior Director of Advanced Analytics and Data Science, the Director of Decision Analytics is focused on building the core analytical methods and tools to enable internal business teams to make better, faster, and more informed decisions around domains such as customer and marketing performance.
        Responsibilities
        Decision Analytics Strategy
        * In partnership with Senior Director of Advanced Analytics and Data Science, develop the strategic roadmap for decision analytic capabilities (i.e. measurement systems for marketing/customer performance, simulation/forecasting methods, scenario planning) to drive business and customer outcomes
        Decisions Analytics
        * Lead a team of Data Analysts to establish enterprise-wide customer analytics methods and tools to make better, faster, and more informed decisions across a wide variety of domains, such as marketing, customer behavior, experience, and product
        * Establish processes and lead method development to enable building decision analytics at scale
        * Champion using best practices and external vendor/partner to accelerate progress where appropriate
        Talent Development
        * Develop and mentor members of the Decision Analytics team
        * Build a talent roadmap to meet the needs of the business
        * Evolve the capabilities of the team as required to support the business
        Qualifications
        * 7+ years of experience developing and applying customer analytics
        * 5+ years of technical experience in tools such as R, Python, or SAS
        * 3+ years of building and leading high performing teams
        * Prior experience developing and performing customer marketing effectiveness measurement for an omni-channel retailer highly desirable
        * Deep knowledge of retail and ecommerce customer domains highly desirable
